The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE ALBUM

 (Landmark, Rs 799)

 The woman with the silky smooth voice who sang Smooth Operator. That?s how Sade may be best known, but discover more about this Nigerian beauty in this set of 1994 performances. High points among the 18 songs are hits like The Sweetest Taboo, No Ordinary Love, and, of course, Smooth Operator.

 THE BOOK

 (Crossword, 6.30 pm, November 7)

 Author Neelum Saran Gour will read excerpts from her novel, Sikandar Chowk Park, which will be followed by a discussion.

 THE TV SHOW 

 (Cartoon Network, noon, November 6)

 Catch the Indian TV premiere of the 18th in Herge?s comic-strip series. The story is set in a world of global espionage as Tintin sets out to search for the kidnapped Professor Calculus, Captain Haddock and Snowy in tow.




